isFoundAfterFileMarker

public boolean isFoundAfterFileMarker(ByteReader targetFile,
                                      boolean reverseOrder,
                                      boolean bigEndian)
Searches for this subsequence after the current file marker position in the file. Moves the file marker to the end of this subsequence.

Parameters:
targetFile - the binary file to be identified
reverseOrder - true if file is being searched from right to left
bigEndian - True iff our parent signature is big-endian
Returns:
boolean
